      "message": "The attribute array, and the marker names, are now stored in the single allocation block, like the vertex data. Specifically:\n\n[SkVertices][Attributes][NullTerminatedStrings][Positions][...]\n\nThe Attribute structs have their char* fMarkerName fields pointing into the block of null-terminated strings stored immediately after.\n\nThis lets us keep the previous behavior, where SkVertices is always a single heap allocation. However, it complicates the string management in several places, and we\u0027re not storing explicit lengths, so we always have to re-compute that when copying/comparing/etc...",
